      "name": "Hemolysis index prediction validation — numerical surrogate",
      "description": "Validation result for CFD hemolysis predictions across 5 VAD operating conditions. The supporting activity performed high-fidelity numerical simulation with Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification, covering the full operating envelope. The team asserts this simulation-based approach captures all relevant physics and is functionally equivalent to experimental bench testing, given the controlled boundary conditions and validated sub-models. Hemolysis index predictions fall below the absolute clinical threshold at all operating points with 95% confidence intervals bounded within acceptable limits.",
